actions.comment:
Thanks for reporting this. You're right — every other GL view exposes `GRContext` as a public property, and the Blazor `SKGLView` should too.

As a workaround until this is addressed, you can access the `GRContext` inside your `OnPaintSurface` handler via pattern matching on `e.Surface.Context`:

```csharp
void OnPaintSurface(SKPaintGLSurfaceEventArgs e)
{
    if (e.Surface.Context is GRContext grContext)
    {
        // Use grContext to create additional surfaces
    }
}
```

Note: This only works within the paint callback. The `GRContext` may be null before the first render frame. If you need it outside the callback, cache the reference yourself.
